          <h2>Born from a <span class="gold">Singular</span> Vision</h2>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p class="lead-para">In 1983, Toyota Chairman Eiji Toyoda posed a question that would change the automotive world: "Can we create a car that is the best in the world?" The answer became Lexus.</p>
          <br>
          <p class="body-para">Over six years and a billion dollars of development, sixty designers, twenty-four engineering teams, 2,300 engineers, 220 test drivers, 450 prototypes, and 2.7 million test miles produced the LS 400 — a car that stunned the world in 1989.</p>
          <br>
          <p class="body-para">The vision was clear: marry Japanese craftsmanship and reliability with the luxury expected by the world's most discerning drivers. More than three decades later, Lexus remains the only luxury brand to have never compromised on that promise.</p>
          <br>
          <div class="highlight-para">"From the moment the first LS 400 rolled off the line, it was clear that the world of luxury motoring had been permanently altered."</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-label">Timeline</div>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:32px;">Key <span class="gold">Milestones</span></h3>
          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">1983</div>
              <h4 style="color:var(--white); margin-bottom:6px;">The Challenge Begins</h4>
              <p class="body-para" style="font-size:.9rem;">Eiji Toyoda initiates "F1 Project" — the secret mission to create the world's finest automobile.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">1989</div>
              <h4 style="color:var(--white); margin-bottom:6px;">Lexus Launches</h4>
              <p class="body-para" style="font-size:.9rem;">The LS 400 debuts at Detroit Auto Show, immediately earning the title of world's quietest production car.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">1998</div>
              <h4 style="color:var(--white); margin-bottom:6px;">RX Redefines Luxury SUV</h4>
              <p class="body-para" style="font-size:.9rem;">The original RX 300 becomes the first luxury crossover SUV, creating an entirely new vehicle category.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">2007</div>
              <h4 style="color:var(--white); margin-bottom:6px;">F Performance Division</h4>
              <p class="body-para" style="font-size:.9rem;">The IS F debuts as Lexus's first genuine performance car, powered by a screaming 5.0L V8.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <div class="timeline-year">2024</div>
              <h4 style="color:var(--white); margin-bottom:6px;">Electrified Future</h4>
              <p class="body-para" style="font-size:.9rem;">Lexus commits to an all-electric lineup by 2035, blending the brand's luxury DNA with zero-emission driving.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section style="padding:80px 0 0;">
